Date: Sun, 20 Oct 2024 12:03:53 -0400
Subject: add back main latency recovery

This adds back the latency recovery system that was removed years ago.
This removal is the source of the issue dubbed 'aim freeze' by
players of browser-based FPS games, and is why game developers
suggest using 'clients' with an extremely outdated version of
electron. Just for testing for now.

